subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis
. Specimens of 

S. cyanocephalus

are readily distinguishable from all other species by the pronotum with a longitudinal dark band on midline (
Fig. 1G
); elytra bicolored, with black spot on the anterior portion (
Fig. 1G
); the eighth elytral stria lacking carina on anterior portion; aedeagus with parameres elongate, subrectangular, not excavated ventrally (
Fig. 4F
); and endophallus lacking bristles or microbristles close to the FLP sclerite (
Fig. 5G
).
